main event: A large silver balloon-shaped object was observed by civilian witnesses in Vero Beach, Florida on October 17, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as a large silver balloon-shaped object.
Witnesses were picked up by power company men who had been alarmed by a power shortage, and fragments of the balloon were found on power lines.
The report concludes that the object was a balloon.
There were no photographs of the object, but physical evidence in the form of balloon fragments was recovered.
